Package org.microbean.qualifier

Class Qualifiers<K extends Comparable<? super K>,V>

java.lang.Object
org.microbean.qualifier.Qualifiers<K,V>
Type Parameters:
K - the type borne by the keys of the qualifiers in this Qualifiers
V - the type borne by the values of the qualifiers in this Qualifiers
All Implemented Interfaces:
Constable, Iterable<Map.Entry<K,V>>
public final class Qualifiers<K extends Comparable<? super K>,V> extends Object implements Constable, Iterable<Map.Entry<K,V>>
A Constable, immutable, sorted set of key-value pairs that can be used to further qualify an object for many different purposes.

Keys are sorted according to their natural order.

This is a value-based class.

Values of type K must be members of classes adhering to value-based semantics.

Values of type V must be members of classes adhering to value-based semantics.

Undefined behavior will result if the preceding requirements are not honored.

Author:
Laird Nelson

    • contains

      public final boolean contains(Qualifiers<?,?> other)
      Returns true if this Qualifiers logically contains the supplied Qualifiers.

      A Qualifiers is said to contain another Qualifiers if either:

      • the two Qualifiers instances are identical, or
      • the size of the first Qualifiers is greater than the size of the second Qualifiers, and the entry set of this Qualifiers contains all of the entries in the second Qualifiers' entry set
      Parameters:
      other - the Qualifiers to test; must not be null
      Returns:
      true if this Qualifiers logically contains the supplied Qualifiers
      Throws:
      NullPointerException - if other is null

    • symmetricDifferenceSize

      public final int symmetricDifferenceSize(Qualifiers<?,?> other)
      Returns the size of the symmetric difference between this Qualifiers and the supplied Qualifiers.

      The number returned is always 0 or greater.

      The size of the symmetric difference between two Qualifiers instances is the number of qualifier entries that are in one Qualifiers instance but not in the other.

      Parameters:
      other - the other Qualifiers instance; may be null
      Returns:
      the size of the symmetric difference between this Qualifiers and the supplied Qualifiers; always 0 or greater

    • of

      public static final <K extends Comparable<? super K>, V> Qualifiers<K,V> of(Object... nameValuePairs)
      Returns a Qualifiers consisting of the entries represented by the supplied alternating name-value pairs.

      The supplied nameValuePairs must be an even-numbered array of non-null Object instances, where the zero-based even-numbered elements represent qualifier keys, and the zero-based odd-numbered elements represent qualifier values.

      Type Parameters:
      K - the type borne by the keys of the qualifiers in the returned Qualifiers
      V - the type borne by the values of the qualifiers in the returned Qualifiers
      Parameters:
      nameValuePairs - the name-value pairs as described above; may be null in which case the return value of the of() method will be returned
      Returns:
      a Qualifiers consisting of the entries represented by the supplied alternating name-value pairs
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if an even number of arguments is not supplied
      ClassCastException - if elements in the supplied array at even positions (0, 2, 4â€¦) are not of type K
      NullPointerException - if any argument is null
      Idempotency:
      This method is idempotent and deterministic.
      Nullability:
      This method never returns null.
      Thread Safety:
      This method is safe for concurrent use by multiple threads.
